Postsecondary Education and Earnings

Postsecondary Education and Voting

Data Sources

  • United States Census Bureau, Tiger Shapefiles: Geographic boundary information from census block to state level
  • Census Bureau, American Community Survey: 2.3 million respondents (Public Use Microdata Sample)
  • National Center for Education Statistics,Integrated Postsecondary Education Data System (IPEDS): Data on ~4,500 institutions of higher education in the United States
  • Bureau of Labor Statistics, National Longitudinal Survey of Youth, 1997 (NLSY97): Longitudinal data on ~9,000 individuals who were between 14-18 in 1997.
  • Educational Longitudinal Survey: Longitudinal data on ~16,000 individuals who were high school sophomores as of 2002.

Tools

  • R as both statistical programming language and GIS
  • RStudio as IDE
  • Git/Github for version control/collaboration
  • Gitter for project related communication
  • Leaflet for spatial visualization
  • D3 for interactive graphics
